00:10:01.830 --> 00:10:05.780
When I think of my childhood,
I remember the old days,

00:10:05.780 --> 00:10:11.590
when I was a little girl, with
black braided hair like goat horns.

00:10:11.590 --> 00:10:16.620
In summer, my five siblings and
I would sit on a wooden bed,

00:10:16.620 --> 00:10:21.100
the huge bed my father made
in the middle of the yard.

00:10:21.100 --> 00:10:23.900
First, we threw little
rugs on the bed,

00:10:23.900 --> 00:10:27.070
then we fought to get
the best corner.

00:10:27.070 --> 00:10:29.220
The breeze was our playmate.

00:10:29.220 --> 00:10:31.510
She brushed our faces.

00:10:31.510 --> 00:10:35.540
Cooled our hearts, slapped
the mosquitoes and flies.

00:10:35.540 --> 00:10:40.060
Like a scented friend, it
carried the aroma of flowers

00:10:40.060 --> 00:10:43.790
and wheat from farther fields.

00:10:43.790 --> 00:10:48.780
Our house, in a vast meadow
with a few other houses,

00:10:48.780 --> 00:10:53.450
was a little flower in a bare
garden, but we didn't feel alone.

00:10:53.450 --> 00:10:56.630
God was also our neighbor.

00:10:56.630 --> 00:10:59.950
We laughed on the wooden--
we laughed on the wooden bed,

00:10:59.950 --> 00:11:04.020
drank black tea, and
played with marbles

00:11:04.020 --> 00:11:10.240
as our white dog jumped
happily, circling the bed like as

00:11:10.240 --> 00:11:12.790
if it's were a sacred shrine.

00:11:12.790 --> 00:11:19.030
I loved her small puppies rolling
on the dusty ground with them,

00:11:19.030 --> 00:11:25.220 position:56%
swirling them around by their little
paws and bursting into laughter.

00:11:25.220 --> 00:11:28.960
They were like balls of
cotton and I kissed their paws

00:11:28.960 --> 00:11:31.820
and caressed them with love.

00:11:31.820 --> 00:11:35.700
Some neighbors said,
"Dogs are Najis, filthy."

00:11:35.700 --> 00:11:37.930
But I treasured them.

00:11:37.930 --> 00:11:42.850
They played with us, they protected
our house, barking at strangers

00:11:42.850 --> 00:11:47.830
and enemies, their yelps
very small and screechy,

00:11:47.830 --> 00:11:50.790
but their will was strong.

00:11:50.790 --> 00:11:53.520
How could anyone call
them "unclean"?

00:11:53.520 --> 00:11:55.820
They were little angels.

00:11:55.820 --> 00:11:58.860
God wouldn't create filthy things.

00:11:58.860 --> 00:12:02.840
Sometimes we didn't have bread
in the house, I was hungry,

00:12:02.840 --> 00:12:06.890
so mother gave me a
piece of dried bread,

00:12:06.890 --> 00:12:09.310
and said "Share it with the dog.

00:12:09.310 --> 00:12:11.490
She is also hungry."

00:12:11.490 --> 00:12:15.850
Her kindness reminds me of when
she cooked okra with Kichiri.

00:12:15.850 --> 00:12:19.000
We sat on the wooden bed
and we ate in the moonlight.

00:12:19.000 --> 00:12:25.620
We didn't have electricity, but
our hearts were bright and happy.

00:12:25.620 --> 00:12:29.860
As we laughed, our teeth
shone like the stars.

00:12:29.860 --> 00:12:32.300
We named the stars to own them.

00:12:32.300 --> 00:12:34.840
My eyes like a basket.

00:12:34.840 --> 00:12:40.020
I picked them until they escaped
from my eyes and entered my heart.

00:12:40.020 --> 00:12:45.090
In my best childhood memories,
we were all together, me,

00:12:45.090 --> 00:12:49.570
my siblings, my mother, my father.

00:12:49.570 --> 00:12:53.460
We weren't yet broken
by war or separated,

00:12:53.460 --> 00:12:57.130
each thrown to a corner
of the earth.

00:12:57.130 --> 00:13:00.660
With free minds and happy
hearts, we laughed together

00:13:00.660 --> 00:13:03.550
and adored simple things.

00:13:03.550 --> 00:13:08.510
On the wooden bed, we
were kings and queens.

