00:15:27.030 --> 00:15:29.020
&gt;&gt; Marzia: "War".

00:15:29.020 --> 00:15:31.330
To buy his family's safety,

00:15:31.330 --> 00:15:37.150
your father spends every Afghani
he has saved for the last 30 years.

00:15:37.150 --> 00:15:40.760
Your mother sells her
jewelry so she can feed you

00:15:40.760 --> 00:15:43.510
and your brothers and sisters.

00:15:43.510 --> 00:15:49.260
Your brother gives up his beloved
car, and you give up your education

00:15:49.260 --> 00:15:52.140
because you have no other option.

00:15:52.140 --> 00:15:55.900
Gunfire and rockets,
like the devil screaming,

00:15:55.900 --> 00:15:58.190
wake you up in the
middle of the night.

00:15:58.190 --> 00:16:01.170
The explosions vibrate
through your heart.

00:16:01.170 --> 00:16:06.110
Nothing can calm you, not
even your mother's arms.

00:16:06.110 --> 00:16:08.280
You see torn bodies on the TV.

00:16:08.280 --> 00:16:11.640
Mothers like crying over
their sons' corpses.

00:16:11.640 --> 00:16:13.810
Widows weep for their children.

00:16:13.810 --> 00:16:16.100
Who will feed them today?

00:16:16.100 --> 00:16:20.520
War means living in fear,
with families torn apart.

00:16:20.520 --> 00:16:23.200
Flowers lose their
color, become gray.

00:16:23.200 --> 00:16:27.020
Dark circles under your
eyes, your skin pale.

00:16:27.020 --> 00:16:32.620 position:56%
You see everything in black and
white, cannot feel the sun's warmth,

00:16:32.620 --> 00:16:36.530
the wind's breeze, see how
bright the moon and the stars.

00:16:36.530 --> 00:16:39.240
Your best friend flees
to another place.

00:16:39.240 --> 00:16:42.620
You miss her, become
lonely, isolated.

00:16:42.620 --> 00:16:47.270
She was the one you shared your
secrets with and played with.

00:16:47.270 --> 00:16:52.790
You don't feel safe without her,
not even in your own bedroom.

00:16:52.790 --> 00:16:54.150
War means poverty.

