00:20:31.470 --> 00:20:34.650
And I wrote this in 2011.

00:20:34.650 --> 00:20:40.970
I didn't know the meaning of
culture shock before I came

00:20:40.970 --> 00:20:44.680
to the United States, but now I do.

00:20:44.680 --> 00:20:46.880
As an international student coming

00:20:46.880 --> 00:20:52.140
from a religious conservative
country like Afghanistan to study

00:20:52.140 --> 00:20:56.590
in a liberal, democratic
country like the US,

00:20:56.590 --> 00:21:02.610
the move definitely shocked my
nerves and appetite for a while.

00:21:02.610 --> 00:21:08.450
When I first arrived, it
was the superficial matters

00:21:08.450 --> 00:21:11.530
that grabbed my attention,
like clothing,

00:21:11.530 --> 00:21:15.020
talking, hairstyle, and fashion.

00:21:15.020 --> 00:21:19.700
I was shocked the first time
I saw women wearing bikinis

00:21:19.700 --> 00:21:23.360
in the public near the beach.

00:21:23.360 --> 00:21:27.250
We have public bathhouse
for women in my country,

00:21:27.250 --> 00:21:31.730
but what embarrassed me was
seeing the women talking

00:21:31.730 --> 00:21:34.330
to men who were with them.

00:21:34.330 --> 00:21:39.830
The men had a live view of
99% of the woman's naked body.

00:21:39.830 --> 00:21:43.580
I may have shocked them as
well, because I was walking

00:21:43.580 --> 00:21:48.360
on the beach fully
dressed with my scarf on.

00:21:48.360 --> 00:21:54.430
Afghans are always trying to avoid
the sun so they will not get tanned

00:21:54.430 --> 00:21:58.830
but some Americans love
to be out in the sun,

00:21:58.830 --> 00:22:03.590
even though they know
about skin cancer.

00:22:03.590 --> 00:22:08.350
Also, tattoos are common here,

00:22:08.350 --> 00:22:12.450
but seeing whole body
tattoo was shocking.

00:22:12.450 --> 00:22:15.220
What if the design
gets boring next year?

00:22:15.220 --> 00:22:20.000
Or what if a man's
wife does not like it?

00:22:20.000 --> 00:22:27.330
Pets, especially dogs, are dear
in this country, sometimes dearer

00:22:27.330 --> 00:22:29.700
and closer than family members.

00:22:29.700 --> 00:22:36.400
I did not know how hard it was
to take care of them, bathe them,

00:22:36.400 --> 00:22:40.380
and feed them or even
play with them!

00:22:40.380 --> 00:22:46.630 position:56%
Yes, in the United States, they even
have vaccinations for their pets.

00:22:46.630 --> 00:22:50.980
We just started the vaccination
process for children in our country

00:22:50.980 --> 00:22:56.490
and almost half of the population
has never ever had a vaccine

00:22:56.490 --> 00:22:58.760
in their lives.

00:22:58.760 --> 00:23:01.500
It is still shocking for me to know

00:23:01.500 --> 00:23:07.750
that in some countries animals
are as valuable as humans.

00:23:07.750 --> 00:23:12.870
Also, I still cannot eat
rice properly with a fork.

00:23:12.870 --> 00:23:15.640
It's frustrating seeing
the grains escape

00:23:15.640 --> 00:23:18.900
from the prongs when I am hungry.

00:23:18.900 --> 00:23:22.360
It is interesting how forks
and knives are important

00:23:22.360 --> 00:23:26.130
in most of the meals in the US.

00:23:26.130 --> 00:23:32.050
In Afghanistan, I only use a knife
for peeling and cutting fruits.

00:23:32.050 --> 00:23:36.780
I think that it is polite
when Americans say "Excuse me"

00:23:36.780 --> 00:23:44.760
